billEvents.eventText: REFERRED TO CULTURAL AFFAIRS, TOURISM, PARKS AND RECREATION

title: Provides free golf for veterans at state park golf courses
summary: Provides that a person who is a veteran of the wars of the United States be permitted to use any of the state park golf courses in this state without the payment of any fees or other charges for the use of such state park golf courses.
currentCommittee: CULTURAL AFFAIRS, TOURISM, PARKS AND RECREATION
lawSection: Parks, Recreation and Historic Preservation Law
actClause: AN ACT to amend the parks, recreation and historic preservation law, in relation to providing free golf for veterans at state park golf courses
